XML_TEMPLATES.name: sap.chart.Chart
XML_TEMPLATES.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Chart. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getChartType chartType} : string (default: bar)
    • {@link #getUiConfig uiConfig} : object
    • {@link #getVisibleDimensions visibleDimensions} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getInResultDimensions inResultDimensions} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getVisibleMeasures visibleMeasures} : string[] (default: [])
    • {@link #getVizProperties vizProperties} : object
    • {@link #getVizScales vizScales} : object[]
    • {@link #getIsAnalytical isAnalytical} : boolean
    • {@link #getSelectionBehavior selectionBehavior} : sap.chart.SelectionBehavior (default: DataPoint)
    • {@link #getSelectionMode selectionMode} : sap.chart.SelectionMode (default: Multi)
    • {@link #getEnablePagination enablePagination} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getEnableStableColor enableStableColor} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getEnableScalingFactor enableScalingFactor} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getCustomMessages customMessages} : object
    • {@link #getColorings colorings} : object
    • {@link #getActiveColoring activeColoring} : object
    • {@link #getValueAxisScale valueAxisScale} : object
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getData data} : sap.ui.core.Element[]
    • {@link #getDimensions dimensions} : sap.chart.data.Dimension[]
    • {@link #getMeasures measures} : sap.chart.data.Measure[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:drilledDown drilledDown} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:drilledUp drilledUp} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:renderComplete renderComplete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:selectData selectData} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:deselectData deselectData} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:valueAxisFixedScaleTurnedOff valueAxisFixedScaleTurnedOff} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:drillStackChanged drillStackChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.viz.ui5.controls.common.BaseControl#constructor sap.viz.ui5.controls.common.BaseControl} can be used as well.

XML_TEMPLATES.name: sap.chart.data.Dimension
XML_TEMPLATES.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ui5/data/Dimension. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getName name} : string
    • {@link #getLabel label} : string
    • {@link #getTextFormatter textFormatter} : function
    • {@link #getTextProperty textProperty} : string
    • {@link #getDisplayText displayText} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getRole role} : string (default: category)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Element#constructor sap.ui.core.Element} can be used as well.
XML_TEMPLATES.helpDescription:
Definition of a single dimension in a chart
chartType binding rules
pie, donut All dimensions are assigned to feed uid “color”.
scatter, bubble All dimensions with role category are assigned to feed uid “shape”.
heatmap All dimensions with role “series” and “category2” are assigned to the feed uid “categoryAxis2”.
treemap All dimensions are assigned to the feed uid “categoryAxis” in the default sequence.

XML_TEMPLATES.name: sap.chart.data.Measure
XML_TEMPLATES.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ui5/data/Measure. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getName name} : string
    • {@link #getLabel label} : string
    • {@link #getUnitBinding unitBinding} : string
    • {@link #getValueFormat valueFormat} : string
    • {@link #getRole role} : string (default: axis1)
    • {@link #getSemantics semantics} : sap.chart.data.MeasureSemantics (default: Actual)
    • {@link #getSemanticallyRelatedMeasures semanticallyRelatedMeasures} : object
    • {@link #getAnalyticalInfo analyticalInfo} : object
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Element#constructor sap.ui.core.Element} can be used as well.
XML_TEMPLATES.helpDescription:
Definition of a single measure in a chart
chartType binding rules
pie, donut The measure is assigned to feed uid “size”.
scatter The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis”. The other measure is assigned to feed uid “valueAxis2”.
bubble The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis”.
The first measure with role “axis2”, or (if not exists) the second measure with role “axis1” or (if not exist) the first measure with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “valueAxis2”.
The remaining measure is assigned to feed uid “bubbleWidth”.
heatmap The measure is assigned to the feed uid “color”.
treemap The first measure with role “axis1”, or (if not exists) the first measure with role “axis2” or (if not exist) with role “axis3”, is assigned to the feed uid “color”. The other measure is assigned to feed uid “weight”.
..dual.. At least one measure is assigned to each of the feed uids “valueAxis” and “valueAxis2”, according to the general rule.
